beer.beer_description:
The beer gods were kind this harvest. Angels sang and celestial light streamed from the van as craft evangelist Carl Vasta parted the doors to reveal botanic riches within. “Let there be Riwaka hops” was heard from above as we shielded our eyes from the glare. Join
our worship of the green hop by accepting our offering, Vastafarian.

Taste: An explosion of passionfruit, gooseberry and grapefruit that only the freshest Nelson Riwaka and Sauvin hops can provide.
Hops: Riwaka and Sauvin.
Malt: American Pale and Light Crystal.
Aroma: Grapefruit, gooseberry and citrus notes.
Look: Golden Pale Ale.
Alcohol/Vol: 5.6%
Bitterness: 45 IBU
Try it with: Spit-roasted pork.
Available: Tap, 500mL bottle.
